article.headline: Detroit 77, Canisius 74
article.story: BUFFALO N.Y. (AP) -- Elijah Warren scored 23 points to lead Detroit over Canisius 77-74 Saturday afternoon. Leading 38-29 at halftime, Detroit (5-3) built as much as a 15-point lead in the second half before Canisius (4-6) went on a 13-1 run to come within 67-64 with 1:05 to play, but the Golden Griffins couldn't take the lead. James Thues finished with 18 points and three steals for Detroit and Willie Wallace had 12. Dewitt Doss led Canisius with 22 points, while Toby Foster had 14 and Downey 13.
